# Futrob design system

The canonical specification is `product/design-system-spec.md`. Futrob is a competition control room for EA FC Clubs: dense for operators, clear for spectators, anchored on EA-sourced matches and auditable official selection.

## Visual principles

1. Prefer continuous rows and tables for encounters, EA candidates, rosters, and rankings. Reserve cards for autonomous entities or framed tools.
2. Keep scores centered, stable, high-contrast, and tabular.
3. Express every status with text plus icon or shape; color is supplementary.
4. Visually separate EA candidates from approved official results.
5. Use compact desktop density and at least 44 px touch targets on mobile.
6. Avoid nested cards, uniform dashboard grids, generic purple gradients, pervasive glass effects, and heavy shadows.
7. Use one component language: shadcn on Base UI for behavior, Futrob tokens for identity.

## Identity and tokens

- Display: Barlow Condensed 600/700 for hero, competition headings, and large scores.
- UI: Manrope 400–700.
- Data: IBM Plex Mono 500/600 for scores, time, and short IDs.
- Semantic CSS variables are the source of truth for component color.
- Green means primary action, approved state, or winner path — not ambient decoration.
- Dark is the principal sports presentation; light remains fully supported. Target WCAG 2.2 AA.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Shells

- Landing: brand-first hero, one promise, one support sentence, CTA group, dominant product visual. No card grid in the first viewport.
- Authenticated desktop: contextual sidebar, app header, page header, filters, fluid content.
- Public competition pages: competition header and sticky tabs without an admin sidebar.

## Match Center

Encounter rows show round/date, both teams, centered score/status, and metadata/action. Detail sections cover Overview, Official matches, EA candidates, Selection (with preview), Schedule history, Stats, and permission-gated History/Admin.

Label aggregate series scores explicitly so goals are never confused with match wins.

## Rankings and bracket

- Official table and performance ranking must not share ambiguous titles.
- Bracket views consume a semantic graph and always provide an equivalent accessible list.
- Byes never show fictitious scores.
